<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Investing for Growth): Directors' dealings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIVIEN MACDONALD, Inside Track
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Largest sale of the week was at Industrial Control Services, a control
systems company, Based in Essex, the group supplies equipment to the oil,
gas and petrochemical industries. Its recent final results reflected good
development and a strong order book. Yet, the shares have been
underperforming over the past year.
Two directors have sold stock. Peter Hall, the chairman and chief executive,
disposed of 550,000 shares and Brian Dodds sold 250,000, all at 120p. Both
remain substantial shareholders, on the board with Hall's holding accounting
for more than 9.2m and Dodds 1.2m.
Britton Group makes extruded polythene. Interim results, announced at the
end of September, reflected good growth, with earnings rising from 2.78p to
4.79p. Profits are forecast to grow by a factor of 4.3 in the next year.
Directors buying at this stage can be a positive indicator.
