<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pepper market was somewhat quieter this week, mainly due to holidays in
various countries. Black pepper tended a little easier in light business.
White, however, especially for delivery to the US, remained steady. Supplies
in Malaysia and China are gradually drying up. This week, at a pepper
seminar in Kuching, Malaysia pessimistic estimates for Malaysian 1995-96
pepper production were issued. As carry over stocks of previous years have
been fully liquidated, when demand re-appears prices are expected to
increase further. Muntok white spot was quoted at USDollars 3,650 a tonne
and November/December shipment at Dollars 3,625, cif. Spot black pepper faq
was at Dollars 2,600 a tonne and November/December shipment at Dollars
2,575, cif.
