<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Worldcatch sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Receivers of Worldcatch, the property company which went into receivership
in February with debts of approximately Pounds 39m, have sold the leasehold
interest in a London building for Pounds 36m.
The building, 2-14 Baker Street, comprises 73,495 sq ft of offices, 16,678
sq ft of retail units and a restaurant.
Mr Chris Barlow, joint administrative receiver from Coopers &amp; Lybrand said
the sale followed an extensive marketing campaign. 'As a result I will be in
a position to pay my appointing bank in full.'
</TEXT>
