FT  19 NOV 94 / Brazil buys British warships
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANGUS FOSTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAO PAULO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Brazil's navy is to buy seven warships from Britain for about Pounds 100m in
the second large arms deal between the two countries this year. Brazil is
buying four type 22 frigates and three river class minesweepers which the
British navy put up for sale earlier this year. The frigates, built between
1976 and 1980, are no longer needed following the post-cold war fleet
reduction. In January Westland, the UK helicopter maker, won a Pounds 150m
order for nine Super Lynx helicopters from the Brazilian navy.
